def load_nifti(filename, header=False, verbose=False):
    """Load nifti files"""
    nifti = nib.load(filename)
    if verbose:
        print(' File loaded from:', filename)
        print(' File dimensions : ', nifti.shape)
        print(' Data type :', nifti.get_data_dtype())
    if header:
        return nifti.get_fdata(), nifti.header
    return nifti.get_fdata()

def plot_boxplots(dataframes, column_name, dataframe_names, lesions_only=False):
    # Create a list of traces for the box plots
    traces = []
    for i, dataframe in enumerate(dataframes):
        if lesions_only:
            dataframe = dataframe[dataframe.num_true_lesions > 0]
        traces.append(go.Box(
            y=dataframe[column_name],
            name=dataframe_names[i]
        ))

    # Create a figure and add the traces
    fig = go.Figure(traces)

    # Update the layout of the figure
    fig.update_layout(
        title="Box Plots",
        yaxis_title=column_name
    )

    # Show the figure
    fig.show()

def plot_errors(dataframes, column_name,names, lesion_only=True):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    for i, df in enumerate(dataframes):
        if lesion_only:
            df = df[df.num_true_lesions > 0]
        mean = df[column_name].mean()
        std = df[column_name].std()
        count = df[column_name].count()
        error = std / (count ** 0.5)  # Standard error of the mean
        ax.bar(i, mean, yerr=error, capsize=5, label=f'{names[i]}')  # Solid bar with error caps
        ax.vlines(i, mean - error, mean + error, color='red', linestyle='-', lw=2)  # Vertical line for standard error

    ax.set_xticks(range(len(dataframes)))
    ax.set_xticklabels([f'{names[i]}' for i in range(len(dataframes))],
                       rotation=45, ha='right')
    ax.set_xlabel('Models')
    ax.set_ylabel(column_name)
    plt.show()

def plot_correlation(df_list, column1, column2, names, lesion_only = True):
    # Calculate the number of rows and columns for subplots
    num_rows = len(df_list)
    num_cols = 1  # You can adjust this depending on how you want to arrange the subplots

    # Create subplots
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_rows, num_cols, figsize=(6, 4 * num_rows))

    # Flatten the axes if there is only one row
    axes = axes.flatten() if num_rows > 1 else [axes]

    # Iterate through the list of dataframes and plot correlations
    for idx, (df, ax) in enumerate(zip(df_list, axes)):
        if lesion_only:
            df = df[df.num_true_lesions > 0]
        # Calculate correlation
        correlation = df[column1].corr(df[column2])

        # Create a scatter plot with regression line
        sns.regplot(x=column1, y=column2, data=df, ax=ax)

        # Set subplot title with the correlation value
        ax.set_title(f'{names[idx]} - Correlation: {correlation:.2f}')

    # Adjust layout to prevent overlapping titles
    plt.tight_layout()

    # Show the plot
    plt.show()

def calc_metrics(preds, target, bcm, epsilon=1e-9):
    cm = bcm(preds.reshape(-1), target.reshape(-1))
    tn = cm[0,0]
    fp = cm[0,1]
    fn = cm[1,0]
    tp = cm[1,1]

    precision = tp / (fp + tp + epsilon)
    recall = tp / (fn + tp + epsilon)
    f1 = (2*precision*recall)/(precision+recall+epsilon)
    dice_score = dice(preds, target).cpu().numpy()
    acc = (tp+tn)/(tp+tn+fp+fn)

    pred_labels = measure.label(preds.reshape(64,64).cpu().numpy(), background=0)
    target_labels = measure.label(target.reshape(64,64).cpu().numpy(), background=0)

    num_preds = len(np.unique(pred_labels)) - 1
    num_lesions = len(np.unique(target_labels)) - 1

    return {'precision' : precision.cpu().numpy(),
            'recall' : recall.cpu().numpy(),
            'f1': f1.cpu().numpy(),
            'dice': dice_score,
            'accuracy': acc.cpu().numpy(),
            'num_true_lesions': num_lesions,
            'num_pred_lesions': num_preds}

def calc_coords(idx, minc, maxc, patch_size, margin):
    """
    Calculate coordinates of the patches in the image
    idx: # of the possible patches
    minc : minimum col value
    maxc : maximum col value
    patch_size : size of patch
    margin : overlaping pixels
    """
    start = minc + idx*margin
    end = minc + idx*margin + patch_size
    if end > maxc:
        diff = end - maxc
        start = start - diff
        end = end - diff
    if start < 0:
        end = end - start
        start = minc
    return start, end

def evaluate_2d_slices(model, patient_id, data_directory, target_directory, time_A, time_B,
                   instance=0, target_size=(512,512), device="cuda:1",
                  file_pattern = "{}/{}/ses-{}/anat/{}_ses-{}_{}.nii.gz"):
    flair_A, header = load_nifti(file_pattern.format(data_directory,
                                            patient_id, time_A,
                                            patient_id, time_A,
                                            "FLAIR"), header=True)
    flair_B = load_nifti(file_pattern.format(data_directory,
                                            patient_id, time_B,
                                            patient_id, time_B,
                                            "FLAIR"))
    lesion_A = load_nifti(file_pattern.format(data_directory,
                                            patient_id, time_A,
                                            patient_id, time_A,
                                            "ground_truth"))
    lesion_B = load_nifti(file_pattern.format(data_directory,
                                            patient_id, time_B,
                                            patient_id, time_B,
                                            "ground_truth"))
    mask = load_nifti(file_pattern.format(data_directory,
                                            patient_id, time_A,
                                            patient_id, time_A,
                                            "defacemask"))
    bcm = BinaryConfusionMatrix().to(device)
    difference = ((lesion_B - lesion_A)> 0)*1
    x_lim, y_lim, z_lim = flair_A.shape
    # extract only those z_slices where the mask is non-zero
    x, y, z = mask.nonzero()
    num_patches = 0
    x_slices = np.unique(x)
    y_slices = np.unique(y)
    z_slices = np.unique(z)
    y_min = np.min(y_slices)
    y_max = np.max(y_slices)
    z_min = np.min(z_slices)
    z_max = np.max(z_slices)
    margin=target_size[0]
    df = []
    prediction_volume = np.zeros(mask.shape)
    for x_slice in x_slices:
        yz_msk_slice = difference[x_slice]
        pred_slice = np.zeros(yz_msk_slice.shape)
        img1_slice = flair_A[x_slice]
        img2_slice = flair_B[x_slice]
        
        #print(yz_msk_slice.shape)
        slc_ymax, slc_zmax = yz_msk_slice.shape
        n_rows, n_cols = slc_ymax//margin, slc_zmax//margin
        
        for i in range(n_rows):
            v_start, v_end = calc_coords(i, y_min, y_max, target_size[0], margin)
            for j in range(n_cols):
                h_start, h_end = calc_coords(j, z_min, z_max, target_size[1], margin)
                msk = yz_msk_slice[v_start:v_end, h_start:h_end]
                x1 = img1_slice[v_start:v_end, h_start:h_end]
                x2 = img2_slice[v_start:v_end, h_start:h_end]
                
                msk = torch.from_numpy(msk.astype(np.int32)).to(device).unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0)
                x1 = torch.from_numpy(x1.astype(np.float32)).to(device).unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0)
                x2 = torch.from_numpy(x2.astype(np.float32)).to(device).unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0)
                
                output = Fn.sigmoid(model(x1,x2))
                df.append(calc_metrics(output, msk, bcm))
                
                pred_slice[v_start:v_end, h_start:h_end] = output.squeeze().cpu().numpy()
        prediction_volume[x_slice] = pred_slice
    
    pred_image = nib.Nifti1Image(prediction_volume, None, header)
    filename = f"{target_directory}{patient_id}_{instance}.nii.gz"
    nib.save(pred_image, filename)
                
    return pd.DataFrame(df)

def eval_paired_patches(model,data_df, data_directory, target_directory, consecutive_pairs=False,
                         target_size=(512,512), device="cuda:1"):
    data = []
    for patient_id, grp in tqdm(data_df.groupby('participant_id')):
        num_sessions = grp['sessions'].values[0]
        changes = [grp[f"observed_change_t{i}"].values[0] for i in range(2,num_sessions+1)]
        if consecutive_pairs:
            # extract only consecutive pairs with change
            for i in range(1, num_sessions+1):
                if changes[i-1]:
                    data.append(evaluate_2d_slices(model, patient_id, data_directory,
                                                  target_directory, i, i+1, device=device,
                                                   instance=i, target_size=target_size,))
                    
        else:
            previous_state = -1
            instance = 0
            for time_1 in range(1, num_sessions):
                for time_2 in range(time_1+1, num_sessions+1):
                    if changes[time_2-2]:
                        if previous_state != 0:
                            #extract pairwise slices
                            data.append(evaluate_2d_slices(model, patient_id, data_directory,
                                                  target_directory, time_1, time_2,
                                                  instance=instance, device=device,
                                                  target_size=target_size))
                            instance+=1
                previous_state = changes[time_1-1]
                
    return pd.concat(data)

def plot_slices(true_f, pred_f):
    gt = nib.load(true_f)
    pred = nib.load(pred_f)
    
    gt = gt.get_fdata()
    pred = pred.get_fdata()
    
    x,y,z = gt.nonzero()
    px, py, pz = pred.nonzero()
    az = np.unique(np.concatenate((z, pz)))
                   
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=len(az), ncols=2, figsize=(10, 90))
    for i,sz in enumerate(az):
        gt_slc = gt[:,:,sz]
        pred_slc = pred[:,:,sz]
        axes[i, 0].imshow(gt_slc,cmap='gray')
        axes[i, 0].set_xticks([])
        axes[i, 0].set_yticks([])
        axes[i, 0].set_title(f'true: slice={sz}')
        axes[i, 1].imshow(pred_slc,cmap='gray')
        axes[i, 1].set_xticks([])
        axes[i, 1].set_yticks([])
        axes[i, 1].set_title(f'pred: slice={sz}')

from skimage import io
import regex as re 
def get_patient_info(filename):
    pat_id, instance, slc = re.findall("\d+", filename)
    return pat_id, instance, int(slc)

def plot_preds(pat_list, pat_id, inst, gt_dir, pred_dir):
    slices = pat_list[pat_id][inst]['slice']
    indexs = pat_list[pat_id][inst]['idx']
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=len(slices), ncols=2, figsize=(10, 200))
    print(slices)
    for i, slc in enumerate(slices):
        gt_slc = io.imread(f"{gt_dir}test_sub-ID{pat_id}_{inst}_{slc}.png")
        pred_slc = io.imread(f"{pred_dir}test_{indexs[i]}.png")
        axes[i, 0].imshow(gt_slc,cmap='gray')
        axes[i, 0].set_xticks([])
        axes[i, 0].set_yticks([])
        axes[i, 0].set_title(f'true: slice={slc}')

    file_pattern = f"subID{patient_id}_{instance}.nii.gz"
    file_path = [f for f in os.listdir(model_dir) if f.startswith(file_pattern)]

    if file_path:
        # Read the NIfTI file using nibabel
        img = nib.load(os.path.join(model_dir, file_path[0]))
        data = img.get_fdata()

        # Display the slice
        axes[i + 2].imshow(data[:, :, slc], cmap="gray")
        axes[i + 2].set_title(model_names[i])

img = io.imread(os.path.join(orig_dir,"A",f"test_sub-ID{patient_id}_{instance}_{slc}.png"))

axes[0].set_title("t")

def calc_dices(patient, inst, models, base_dir = "/home/prateek/baselines/boundary_aware/stacks/", orig_dir = "/home/prateek/ms_project/change_balcrop256/"):
    dices = {}
    for model in models:
        pred = f"{base_dir}{model}/subID{patient}_{inst}.nii.gz"
        true = f"{base_dir}ground_truth/subID{patient}_{inst}.nii.gz"
        
        for i in len(pred):
            if i in dices.keys():
                dices[i][model] = dice(pred[:,:,i],true[:,:,i])
            else:
                dices[i] = {model: dice}
